HEADWORD: Passeres
<hw>Pas"se*res</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>prop. n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL.,
fr. L. <ets>passer</ets> a sparrow.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>An
order, or suborder, of birds, including more that half of all the known
species. It embraces all singing birds (Oscines), together with many
other small perching birds.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Passeriform</ent>⟦br⟧
